programmes.show_description: A game changing piece of equipment leads the Ferals to their biggest nugget haul of the season. Plus, Shane and Russell battle unseasonal weather. S6, Ep11
Naked And Afraid Of Sharks. On a barren island in shark-infested waters, five all-star competitors must survive for 14 days. Can they live on only what the ocean provides? S5, Ep1

Twin Capes Ferry. The crew heads to Norfolk, Virginia, to test their sea legs and salvage a ferry including lights, skylights and a mural. Grayson helps Mike and Tay with a build. S9, Ep4
Return To The Ferry. The team returns to the Norfolk ferry to get the large items that were left behind, including a crow's nest and staircase. Mike and Robert have a consultation. S9, Ep5
Texas Cold 'Em. Shawn turns to an unusual method to track down a tricky paystreak. Vernon races against weakening ice on Claim 56. Zeke makes a late move to Tomcod. S10, Ep27
Yo Brother, Where Art Thou? With Kris away, Andy is under pressure to bring in gold as captain of the Reaper. Zeke tries Shawn's coordinates to finally get on the gold trail. S10, Ep28
Alan and Salty venture deep into Western Australia's Pilbara region. The Gold Devils struggling to find a reliable source of gold on their Fairlady lease. S9, Ep7
South Africa's Legendary Beast. A recent sighting of a local and bizarre beast, a kaaiman, calls Jeremy to South Africa. He hopes to uncover the facts behind this ancient myth. S1, Ep8
Long Haul, Short Fuses. After 40 hard days at sea the pressure is on and tempers boil over on deck. And the superstitious Captain Keith is upset to have missed a herd of walruses. S5, Ep5
Deadline. A new deadline is set - an upcoming drop in the price of king crab has the skippers rushing to finish their season. But crew battles and a fierce arctic storm block the way. S5, Ep6
Island Of Fortune. Darrell and the team head to a mysterious island where they discover valuable clues that lead them closer in the hunt to a 500-year-old shipwreck. S2, Ep6
The Warrior Queen's Treasure. Josh Gates searches across England to unearth a cache of ancient treasures belonging to the legendary Celtic queen, Boudica. S6, Ep16
The Quest For King Arthur. Josh Gates traverses England, Wales and Scotland, wading through history and legend to search for evidence of a real King Arthur. S2, Ep1
Wolves At The Door. The Raneys help the Johnson family who have no drinking water or food sources. Their dogs have been killed by a mystery predator and worry they are next. S1, Ep7
Trapped. The Raneys assist two Montana homesteaders who face being trapped on their property. When a medical emergency strikes, the Raneys face their first ever failed rescue. S1, Ep8
Wild Wild West. Justin's excavator has an expensive oil leak. Plus, Col's crew are a man down and the Fire Crew are on a wild goose chase hunting a bounty of fabled fire opal. S2, Ep2
Going Under. For the Rookies, there's tension as a new partner leads them on a wild goose chase underground. Plus, the Cooke Brothers' season is off to a bad and dangerous start. S2, Ep3
Bite the Hand. A second major storm hits the fleet. While rookie skipper Jake Anderson reaches out to Sig Hansen for help, Josh Harris arrives on the grounds weeks late. S11, Ep14
New Blood, Old Wounds. Late into Opilio season, the fleet battles against mental & physical breakdown. After deliberately defying Sig, Captain Jake Anderson has a shot at redemption. S11, Ep15
Deep Mud, Deeper State. When state inspectors make a surprise visit to the mine, the Hoffman team races to save their operation before the inspectors return with a verdict. S2, Ep6
The Purpose Of Porpoises. For the first time, Captain Sig faces a man overboard. The tide turns for Johnathan when thousands of porpoises guide the Time Bandit to new grounds. S20, Ep6
The Poseidon Crew are slowed down by fierce storms. Jacqui and Andrew encounter a deadly insect, while the Gold Timers try to fix their dry blower. S6, Ep12
Heart Of Darkness. Nine series veterans try to survive the deadly jungles of Ecuador's Amazon basin for 40 days and 40 nights. Hit by injury and hunger, they're pushed to the edge. S2, Ep1
What Lies Beneath. The seven remaining survivalists enter week two of their brutal challenge in the Amazon. After two tap-outs in the first four days, their priority is to find food. S2, Ep2

Return To K-Town. Mike and Tay build a commemorative clock for the town of Kannapolis, North Carolina, before the crew heads back to salvage items left behind on the first trip. S9, Ep6
Carpenters Hall. The crew stays local and heads just down the street in Roanoke where they salvage a one-of-a-kind sign and pick through an old meeting hall. S9, Ep7
Mining On A Prayer. Kris must move fast in the face of a life-threatening incident. Vernon pushes a diver for a personal record, and Shawn deals with a crack in the ice. S10, Ep29
Legend Vs. Underdog. A massive blizzard is about to hit Nome, Alaska, and bring the mining season to an end. Zeke risks one last move, while Shawn hits a big jackpot. S10, Ep30
Jacqui and Andrew get trapped behind the line of a devastating bushfire. The Gold Devils are torn apart when a team member goes off on their own. S9, Ep8
Hunt Begins, The. Julia's first mission is a giant python in a living room. Then, she tries to catch a snake trapped in an air conditioning box. S1, Ep1
Down to the Wire. The King Crab Season comes down to the wire, as the struggling skippers battle to top off their quotas. Who will land a bumper haul in this end of season sprint? S5, Ep7
Payback Time. It's the start of the 2009 Crab Season, and things are looking up for our spectacular skippers. But will their dreams been shattered by a colossal rogue wave? S5, Ep8
Into The Storm. A dangerous storm threatens to shut down the operation just as Darrell and team discover gold ore in the remains of an old wreck. S2, Ep7
Africa's Cursed Lake Of Gold. Josh Gates journeys to the wilds of Namibia to embark on a treacherously deep dive in Lake Otjikoto for a long lost World War I treasure. S3, Ep11
Gold Rush Of The Atlantic. Josh has a fresh lead on a shipwreck from 1715 with a potentially massive treasure haul. He launches an expedition into Florida's Atlantic coast. S6, Ep4
Drowning. In Hawaii the Raneys attempt to save two homesteaders whose dream homestead lays a flash-flood zone. As the weather closes in, can they save the property from the water? S1, Ep9
Honey I Torched The Homestead. In Oregon, the Raneys are called in to help snowbound homesteaders. Exposed to local predators, they worry about the region's forest fires. S1, Ep10
Risky Business. Justin gambles thousands of dollars as he is struggling this season. Kelly is in desperate need for a big find underground and Aaron and Greg's claim might pay off. S2, Ep4
Hot Hot Hot. The Rookies' relationship is on the rocks as they battle their biggest claim yet. With two partners working at different speeds, there's a fight brewing. S2, Ep5
Beastmode. Superbowl fever hits The Cornelia Marie, an injured crewman creates jeopardy on the Wizard, the Cape Caution makes a near fatal error, and the Time Bandit loses a Captain. S11, Ep16
I'm The Captain. The polar ice descends, threatening the end of season. Sig attempts to offload his crab before saving his gear, and Casey shows Josh what it means to be a Captain. S11, Ep17
A High Steaks Build. The crew kicks off a new waterside build, but a surprise call from the homeowners could change everything. S15, Ep2
Put To The Test. Mark and the guys make the seven-hour trek to Dubois, Indiana, to salvage a cabin picked by the youngest member of the crew. S15, Ep2
